    public interface Self<S extends Self<S>>
extends Copyable<S>
    For classes which follow the self-bounding pattern. The self-bounding pattern is the use of the final derived class as a type parameter.

    Generally only the most specific useful type will be considered for parameterization, and more specific type information will be discarded.
